1. Ask the user to enter NUM1
2. Ask the user to enter the operator
3. Ask the user to enter NUM2
4. Set SUM = NUM1 + NUM2
5. Set DIFFERENCE = NUM1 - NUM2
6. Set PRODUCT = NUM1 * NUM2
7. Set DIVISION = NUM1/NUM2
8. Set REMAINDER = NUM1 % NUM2
9. If the operator is “+”, Display “SUM”
10. If the operator is “-“, Display “DIFFERENCE”
11. If the operator is “*”, Display “PRODUCT”
12. If the operator is “/”, Check NUM2 should not be equals to 0 then Display "DIVISION" Otherwise Display "MATH ERROR"
13. If the operator is “%”, Check NUM2 should not be equals to 0 then Display "REMAINDER" Otherwise Display "MATH ERROR"
